Syntax: ~topratio <word> [guild] [amount=10] [min_total=0]
Prints the members with the highest "word to all words" ratio.
Use the parameter "word" to set the word to compare. Use the optional parameter "guild" to see the ratio in a specific guild. Use the optional parameter "amount" to change the number of members that are displayed. Use the optional parameter "min_total" to change the minimum number of words a user needs to have said to be shown.
Subcommands:
global Prints the members with the highest "word to all words"...
Type ~help <command> for more info on a command. You can also type ~help <category> for more info on a category.

ꜱᴋᴇʟ 2023-01-31 7:40 PM
"star" in Mandarin is 星 xīng, but it's used as a suffix for a lot of space objects. so 彗星 huìxīng means "comet" and 衛星 wèixīng is a satellite or a moon. our moon, however, is 月 yuè, which is also used in dates for "month". so January is 一月 yīyuè, "first month"
